omments%20Solomon%20made%20in%20January%20about%20%26quot%3Ba%20three-year%20program%26quot%3B%20to%20better%20manage%20the%20bank's%20expenses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20discussed%20at%20length%20on%20our%20fourth-quarter%20earnings%20call%2C%20we're%20focused%20on%20operating%20the%20firm%20effectively%20and%20prudently%20over%20the%20long%20term%2C%20managing%20our%20business%20to%20meet%20the%20needs%20of%20our%20clients%20and%20re-investing%20for%20growth%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20Goldman%20spokeswoman%20said%20in%20an%20emailed%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWho%20could%20be%20impacted%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEvery%20year%2C%20Goldman%20Sachs%20cuts%20as%20many%20as%205%25%20of%20its%20bottom%20performers%20through%20a%20process%20known%20internally%20as%20the%20Strategic%20Resource%20Assessment%2C%20or%20SRA.%20Employees%20who%20routinely%20fail%20to%20comply%20with%20Goldman's%20five-day-per-week%20office%20attendance%20policy%2C%20for%20example%2C%20could%20be%20vulnerable%20to%20a%20cut%20through%20the%20SRA%20%E2%80%94particularly%20if%20they're%20found%20to%20be%20underperforming%20in%20their%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20year's%20SRA%2C%20however%2C%20will%20be%20informed%20to%20some%20degree%20by%20%26quot%3BProject%20Voyage%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20ex-Goldman%20insider%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20bank's%20vice%20presidents%20%E2%80%94%20a%20title%20that%20sits%20between%20associate%20and%20managing%20directors%20%E2%80%94%20will%20be%20eyed%20for%20cuts%20in%20part%20because%20Project%20Voyage%20has%20identified%20this%20group%20as%20too%20large%20and%20costly.%20As%20BI%20reported%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20Goldman's%20VP%20ranks%20have%20become%20so%20bloated%20that%20its%20VPs%20have%20been%20increasingly%20reporting%20to%20other%20VPs%20rather%20than%20managing%20directors.%20Compensation%20for%20client-facing%20VPs%20can%20reach%20%241%20million%2C%20including%20base%20salary%20and%20bonuses%2C%20the%20former%20employee%20estimated.%3C%2F