%20US%20about%20the%20dangers%20of%20an%20AI%20Manhattan%20Project.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIn%20the%20paper%2C%20Schmidt%2C%20Dan%20Hendrycks%2C%20and%20Alexandr%20Wang%20push%20for%20a%20more%20defensive%20approach.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20authors%20suggest%20the%20US%20sabotage%20rival%20projects%2C%20rather%20than%20advance%20the%20AI%20frontier%20alone.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20the%20biggest%20names%20in%20AI%20tech%20say%20an%20AI%20%26quot%3BManhattan%20Project%26quot%3B%20could%20have%20a%20destabalizing%20effect%20on%20the%20US%2C%20rather%20than%20help%20safeguard%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20dire%20warning%20came%20from%20former%20Google%20CEO%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feric-schmidt-ai-risks-biological-attacks-rogue-states-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEric%20Schmidt%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Center%20for%20AI%20Safety%20director%20Dan%20Hendrycks%2C%20and%20Scale%20AI%20CEO%20Alexandr%20Wang.%20They%20coauthored%20a%20policy%20paper%20titled%20%26quot%3BSuperintelligence%20Strategy%26quot%3B%20published%20on%20Wednesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20paper%2C%20the%20tech%20titans%20urge%20the%20US%20to%20stay%20away%20from%20an%20aggressive%20push%20to%20develop%20superintelligent%20AI%2C%20or%20AGI%2C%20which%20the%20authors%20say%20could%20provoke%20international%20retaliation.%20China%2C%20in%20particular%2C%20%26quot%3Bwould%20not%20sit%20idle%26quot%3B%20while%20the%20US%20worked%20to%20actualize%20AGI%2C%20and%20%26quot%3Brisk%20a%20loss%20of%20control%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20write.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20authors%20write%20that%20circumstances%20similar%20to%20the%20nuclear%20arms%20race%20that%20birthed%20the%20Manhattan%20Project%20%E2%80%94%20a%20secretive%20initiative%20that%20ended%20in%20the%20creation%20of%20the%20first%20atom%20bomb%20%E2%80%94%20have%20developed%20around%20the%20AI%20frontier.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20November%202024%2C%20for%20example%2C%20a%20bipartisan%20congressional%20committee%20