-office-on-s-jaishankar-security-breach-7862541%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Britain%20said%20the%20police%20acted%20swiftly%20after%20an%20incident%20of%20breach%20of%20security%20of%20External%20Affairs%20Minister%20S%20Jaishankar%20happened%20in%20London%2C%20and%20warned%20that%20%26quot%3Bany%20attempt%20to%20intimidate%20and%20threaten%26quot%3B%20is%20unacceptable.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fstrongly-condemn-uk-foreign-office-on-s-jaishankar-security-breach-7862541%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22H-1B%20Visa%3A%20Why%20US%20Wants%20Employers%20To%20Hire%20Americans%20Over%20Migrant%20Workers%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20Trump%20administration's%20efforts%20to%20challenge%20what%20it%20deems%20as%20illegal%20hiring%20preferences%20for%20foreign%20workers%2C%20particularly%20in%20the%20H-1B%20visa%20program%2C%20has%20caused%20apprehension%20among%20the%20immigrant%20community.%20At%20the%20heart%20of%20this%20controversy%20lies%20the%20Equal%20Employment%20Opportunity%20Commission's%20(EEOC)%20investigation%20into%20the%20matter%2C%20aimed%20at%20safeguarding%20jobs%20for%20US%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20stern%20warning%20issued%20on%20February%2019%2C%202025%2C%20businesses%20were%20cautioned%20against%20prioritising%20foreign%20workers%20over%20American%20candidates%2C%20with%20EEOC's%20acting%20chair%2C%20Andrea%20Lucas%2C%20highlighting%20the%20pervasive%20nature%20of%20national%20origin%20discrimination%20in%20hiring%20across%20multiple%20industries%2C%20according%20to%20a%20Business%20Standard%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noindex%2Cnofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Ffinance%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fh-1b-visa-conundrum-no-anti-american-bias-migrant-preference-warns-us-125030400371_1.html%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BUnlawful%20bias%20against%20American%20workers%2C%20in%20violation%20of%20Title%20VII%2C%20is%20a%20large-scale%20problem%20in%20multiple%20industries%20nationwide%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Lucas.%20%26quot%3BMany%20employers%20have%20policies%20and%20practices%20preferring%20illegal%20aliens%2C%20migrant%20workers%2C%20and%20visa%20holders%20or%20other%20legal%20immigrants%20over%20American%20workers-in%20direct%20violation%20of%20federal%20employment%20law.%20Cracking%20down%20on%20this%20type%20of%20unlawful%20discrimination%20will%20shift%20employer%20incentives%2C%20decreasing%20demand%20for%20illegal%20alien%20workers%20and%20decreasing%20abuse%20of%20the%20United%20States'%20legal%20immigration%20system.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELucas%20added%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20EEOC%20is%20putting%20employers%20and%20other%20covered%20entities%20on%20notice%3A%20if%20you%20are%20part%20of%20the%20pipeline%20contributing%20to%20our%20immigration%20crisis%20or%20abusing%20our%20legal%20immigration%20system%20via%20illegal%20preferences%20against%20American%20workers%2C%20you%20must%20stop.%20The%20law%20applies%20to%20you%2C%20and%20you%20are%20not%20above%20the%20law.%20The%20EEOC%20is%20here%20to%20protect%20all%20workers%20from%20unlawful%20national%20origin%20discrimination%2C%20including%20American%20workers.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20H-1B%20visa%20program%2C%20which%20enables%20US%20companies%20to%20hire%20foreign%20professionals%20in%20fields%20requiring%20a%20degree%2C%20such%20as%20technology%2C%20engineering%20and%20medical%20sciences%2C%20has%20come%20under%20scrutiny.%20Critics%20argue%20that%20this%20program%20displaces%20American%20workers%2C%20with%20some%20employers%20allegedly%20favouring%20foreign%20workers%20due%20to%20lower%20labour%20costs%20that%20get%20achieved%20through%20illegal%20payments%2C%20perceived%20stronger%20work%20ethic%2C%20customer%20preferences%20or%20the%20mindset%20that%20foreign%20workers%20are%20easier%20to%20exploit%20because%20they%20have%20limited%20knowledge%20of%20labour%20rights.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20notable%20example%20is%20the%20lawsuit%20against%20Meta%20Platforms%2C%20which%20alleges%20the%20company%20systematically%20preferred%20visa%20holders%20over%20American%20candidates%20to%20cut%20costs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoth%20the%20Trump%20and%20Biden%20administrations%20have%20introduced%20measures%20to%20tighten%20regulations%20around%20the%20H-1B%20system%2C%20increasing%20scrutiny%20of%20employers%20and%20adjusting%20wage%20requirements.%20However%2C%20experts%20warn%20that%20such%20changes%20could%20have%20far-reaching%20consequences%20for%20Indian%20professionals%2C%20who%20received%2072.3%25%20of%20all%20H-1B%20visas%20issued%20between%20October%202022%20and%20September%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJidesh%20Kumar%2C%20managing%20partner%20at%20King%20Stubb%20%26amp%3B%20Kasiva%2C%20a%20corporate%20law%20firm%2C%20emphasises%20the%20US%20economy's%20reliance%20on%20H-1B%20visas%20to%20address%20skilled%20labour%20shortages%2C%20particularly%20in%20technology%2C%20engineering%2C%20and%20healthcare%2C%20according%20to%20the%20report.%20He%20cautions%20that%20tightening%20the%20program%20could%20drive%20global%20talent%20to%20other%20destinations%20such%20as%20Canada%20or%20the%20UK%2C%20potentially%20undermining%20the%20US's%20position%20as%20a%20leader%20in%20innovation%20and%20economic%20growth.%20%26quot%3BTech%20giants%20and%20startups%20alike%20depend%20on%20H-1B%20professionals%20for%20cutting-edge%20research%20and%20product%20development.%20Many%20also%20go%20on%20to%20become%20entrepreneurs%2C%20creating%20jobs%20and%20boosting%20the%20economy%26quot%3B%2C%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20American%20Immigration%20Council%20disputes%20claims%20that%20the%20H-1B%20program%20harms%20American%20workers%2C%20citing%20research%20that%20shows%20H-1B%20workers%20are%20paid%20well%20above%20national%20averages.%20In%202021%2C%20their%20median%20salary%20was%20%24108%2C000%2C%20compared%20to%20%2445%2C760%20for%20all%20US%20workers.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1741262760000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-03%2F85btsje8_h1b-visa-istock_625x300_06_March_25.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fh-1b-visa-why-us-has-warned-employers-to-hire-americans-over-migrant-workers-how-it-impacts-indians-7862390%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22At%20the%20heart%20of%20this%20controversy%20lies%20the%20Equal%20Employment%20Opportunity%20Commission's%20(EEOC)%20investigation%20into%20the%20matter%2C%20aimed%20at%20safeguarding%20jobs%20for%20US%20workers.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fh-1b-visa-why-us-has-warned-employers-to-hire-americans-over-migrant-workers-how-it-impacts-indians-7862390%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22US%20'destroying'%20world%20order%20by%20trying%20to%20meet%20Russia%20'halfway'%2C%20Ukraine's%20UK%20ambassador%20warns%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1741262760000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F25%2F03%2F1920x1080%2Fskynews-firefighters-ukraine_6847728.jpg%3F20250306080553%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fus-destroying-international-rules-based-order-by-trying-to-meet-russia-halfway-ukraines-uk-ambassador-warns-13322700%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20United%20States%20is%20%26quot%3Bfinally%20destroying%26quot%3B%20the%20international%20rules-based%20order%20by%20trying%20to%20meet%20Russia%20%26quot%3Bhalfway%26quot%3B%2C%20Ukraine's%20ambassador%20to%20the%20UK%20has%20warned.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A10%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fus-destroying-international-rules-based-order-by-trying-to-meet-russia-halfway-ukraines-uk-ambassador-warns-13322700%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%